== Bio ==

Jan Krikke is a former Tokyo correspondent for the Dutch news agency GPD and
the daily Financiële Dagblad, a contributor to IEEE publications, and the former
managing editor of Asia 2000, a book publisher in Hong Kong, and a frequent
contributor to the Asia Times.

Krikke pioneered the study of the origin of [https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/851742 axonometry], the Chinese equivalent of
European linear perspective. He wrote numerous essays on art, science, and
philosophy and is the author of several books, among them [https://www.amazon.com/Leibniz-Einstein-China-Jan-Krikke/dp/9077787445 Leibniz, Einstein, and China]. His most recent book is [https://www.amazon.com/Creating-Planetary-Culture-European-Transcendence/dp/B0CB2FV1K7 Creating a Planetary Culture: European Science, Chinese Art, and Indian Transcendence].

In the 1990s, Krikke edited the book The [[Spiritual Imperative]], a macrohistory
based on the Indian Varna system by futurist [[Larry Taub]] (1936-2016). Taub&#39;s
macrohistory fueled Krikke&#39;s interest in non-Western perspective and the
dynamics that are leading to the development of our planetary culture.

—— supplied by Jan Krikke, 2023

